org.team5940.pantry.logging.loggers

Class PrintStreamLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team5940.pantry.logging.loggers.PrintStreamLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Logger

    public class PrintStreamLogger
extends java.lang.Object
implements Logger
    This implementation of Logger converts each message to a single line of JSON as a string and println()s to a PrintStream. For example, to output logs to the console, you could use "new PrintStreamLogger(System.out)".
    The Gson object used to convert Messages to strings is built with:
    • serializeNulls()
